{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"58185d06-ceed-485d-b677-ed5db570dcdd","content":"There's no pipeline file in this repo, so here's the migration guidance:\n\n**Replace `VSTestRunner@3` with `dotnet test`** using the `DotNetCoreCLI@2` task (or a plain script). Microsoft.Testing.Platform runs via `dotnet test` when your test projects reference `Microsoft.Testing.Platform` and set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`.\n\n### Key changes\n\n**1. Project file** – add to each test `.csproj`:\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Pipeline task** – replace `VSTest@3` with:\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: test\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish test results'\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: VSTest\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n  condition: always()\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  displayName: 'Publish code coverage'\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n**3. For Cobertura format** (recommended for `PublishCodeCoverageResults@2`), add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet and use:\n```\n--collect \"XPlat Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n### Why this works\n- `VSTest@3` invokes `vstest.console`, which doesn't support Microsoft.Testing.Platform.\n- `dotnet test` detects the new platform automatically.\n- TRX logger and coverage collectors work the same way via `--logger` and `--collect`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8e43e46b-f450-4653-ae42-828ff5ad49bb","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"No pipeline files found. This is a general guidance question, not a repo-specific task. Let me provide concise guidance on migrating from VSTest@3 to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX and code coverage.","outputTokens":590,"requestId":"0C0F:348FFE:223A37:2807E7:69F0055B"},"id":"947a2b1b-bd11-42b7-aff7-4c3cb0b7a2f5","timestamp":"2026-04-28T00:55:03.732Z","parentId":"bb3f356f-1b4c-4c7a-aa2f-bddc10e5b0c4"}
